@HEADER	GLOBASH,1,May 2010,GNU Project
@NAME	globash - a special shell for GLOBAL using GNU bash.
@SYNOPSIS
	@name{blobash}
@DESCRIPTION
	@name{Globash} is a special shell for GLOBAL using GNU bash.
	You can use a lot of function to ease reading source code
	like tag stack, tag mark and cookie.
	At first, you should make tag files using @name{gtags} and
	invoke this command in the project.
	Please refer to the help (type 'ghelp'<ENTER>) about a detailed usage.
@FILES
	@begin_itemize
	@item{@file{GTAGS}}
		Tag file for object definitions.
	@item{@file{GRTAGS}}
		Tag file for object references.
	@item{@file{GPATH}}
		Tag file for path of source files.
	@item{@file{~/.globashrc}}
		The personal initialization file, executed for globash.
	@end_itemize
@ENVIRONMENT
	The following environment variables affect the execution of @name{globash}:
	@begin_itemize
	@item{@var{EDITOR}}
		The editor used by the show command.
	@end_itemize
@SEE ALSO
